== Three versions ==

* {{color|blue|text=Blue = Easy}}
* {{color|yellow|text=Yellow = Normal}}
* {{color|purple|text=Purple = Legendary}}

All three versions use the same storyline about an [[Entellan]] rebellion which is only discovered by [[Mister Spock]] using his mind-meld technique ; {{EventText02|12|6}}

=== Storyline ===
==== Trivia ====
* The English-translation for '''Challenge''' (Bonus) level-Titles is missing, the Spanish-word used is Desafio (iirc)...
* On level 6.5, the Easy icons show 3 prizes, but there are actually 4 prizes...
ck=e1-12/m1-12/h1-12

{{#invoke:EventTables|main|Storyline
|D444|Unknown Damage|During a voyage, Scotty reports that the ship's hull was damaged in battle.
|S444|One Week|Spock suggests reviewing the Enterprise's archives to determine when the damage occurred.
|B444|S|.
|D444|Mystery|After the battle, Kirk gathers the crew to try to find out what is going on with them.
|C333|Mind Meld|Spock offers to perform a mind meld, one by one, to try to get to the bottom of this.
|B444|S|.
|S444|Klingon|In the conference room, Spock prepares to mind meld with Doctor McCoy.
|S444|Backup|Back on the Enterprise, it is Uhura's turn.
|B433|C|.
|C444|Rebels|Spock establishes a connection with Chekov, and we return to the planet Tronken-33.
|C333|Tricked|Tataur leads the team to a trap in the hangar, but nothing is what it seems.
|B444|S|.
|S444|Sabotage|It is now Sulu's turn. The Klingons accuse the Enterprise of sabotaging the evacuation.
|D433|Conspiracy|Spock awakens after the explosion and is greeted by an unpleasant surprise.
|B444|C|.
|D444|Accused|A Klingon ship appears and accuses them of manipulating their memories to avoid taking responsibility for what has happened on Tronken-33.
|B333|S|.
|D433|Answers|The crew receives an unexpected visit from Tenva.
}}


