{{#invoke:EventTables|main|Storyline
|S444|Distress Signal|On the way to Lota 3, the Enterprise receives a distress call and decides to act quickly.
|S444|Without Respite|Following the initial confrontation, Captain Kirk attempts to establish communication with the space station, but things aren't so simple.
|B444|C|.
|C444|Salty|When they are finally able to enter the station, Kirk and his team discover they have a serious problem with salt.
|C444|Android|After his unexpected encounter, Kirk must be ready for anything...  but he may be surprised nonetheless.
|B433|S|.
|S444|Permanent Alert!|While Kirk and Spock try to determine what's happened, the rest of the crew will find out that the danger is not only in the space station.
|C444|Devil in the dark|Antonio leads the crew through the space station, with the aim of reaching the command center.
|B333|S|.
|D444|After him!|Arden has taken advantage of the distraction and escaped.  Kirk and Spock won't let him get away without an explanation.
|C444|The Truth|Arden is cornered and pressured by Kirk.  Will he be convincing enough?
|C444|Old Friends|The crew intercepts Arden's shuttle and follows it to a nearby system.
|B333|S|.
|C444|Reunion|Against all odds, two old "friends" meet again.
|D444|Outcome|Following his defeat, our heroes are going to find out if Alvaro is willing to talk.
|B444|C|.
|S333|Fugitive|Alvaro tries to escape, sending another ship to cover his getaway.
|B433|S|.
|S444|The End|The story reaches its inevitable end.
}}


