|S444|Pusuit|During a routine mission in the neutral zone, the crew of the Enterprise will have an unexpected encounter.
|D444|Interrogation|The crew decides to learn everything they can about their new guest, but he seems umwilling to cooperate.
|B444|C|.
|D444|Crossroads|Following Terrhea 's revelations, the crew must decide if they should believe his story and assist the adrift ship.
|S333|Border|The Enterprise is at the edge of the neutral zone, and anything could happen.
|B444|S|.
|S444|Found!|The Enterprise finally finds the adrift ship and discovers that they are not alone.
|C444|Corridors|Riker forms a team and teleports to the ship, hoping to find someone who can tell him where it came from.
|B433|S|.
|C444|Beside Himself|The team continues to investigate the ship and meets another group of Romulans
|B333|S|.
|D444|Against the Ropes|Picard and Troi question Terrhea about the stranded ship.
|C444|Confessions|Terrhea is cornered and forced to reveal his true motives.
|B433|S|.
|S444|Escape|Terrhea escapes and Picard decides to intercept him, but in the meantime new problems arise.
|B444|C|.
|S333|Reinforcement|After disabling Terrhea's ship, Picard is about to capture it, but it will not be an easy task.
|B433|S|.
|D444|No Way Out|Picard has convinced Veidek to hear him out.  Will he be able to persuade the Romulans about Terrhea's true nature ?
